abstract: For at least two decades, the New York City Housing Authority routinely disputed tests that revealed lead in its apartments. Private landlords almost never do this.

abstract: Let’s eliminate money problems from the admissions equation for qualified students.
snippet: Let’s eliminate money problems from the admissions equation for qualified students.

abstract: Wall Street has dominated New York’s economy for too long. Amazon’s HQ2 is a huge opportunity to diversify.
snippet: Wall Street has dominated New York’s economy for too long. Amazon’s HQ2 is a huge opportunity to diversify.
lead_paragraph: For decades, experts have called for the diversification of the New York City economy. In the wake of postwar deindustrialization, our reliance on Wall Street and the financial industry in general had by the 1990s left our city disproportionately vulnerable to swings in the financial markets. We have experienced significant downturns that today feel like distant memories but could certainly return. I know this from my own experience as director of planning for Manhattan after Sept. 11.

abstract: The financial dominance of the National Rifle Association was topped by gun control groups that helped win the House for Democrats.
snippet: The financial dominance of the National Rifle Association was topped by gun control groups that helped win the House for Democrats.
lead_paragraph: Amid a numbing succession of mass shootings, gun control groups outspent the National Rifle Association in the midterm election cycle, federal filings and additional reporting indicate, upending the usual order in the partisan battle over gun use.

abstract: The deal reached between Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo, Mayor Bill de Blasio and Amazon was constructed to blunt the veto power of local politicians.
snippet: The deal reached between Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo, Mayor Bill de Blasio and Amazon was constructed to blunt the veto power of local politicians.
lead_paragraph: The deal to bring Amazon to Long Island City, at a cost of more than $2 billion in government incentives, has sparked outrage in many corners of New York City, particularly in Queens, where residents and elected officials have vowed resistance.

lead_paragraph: Hi. Welcome to On Politics, your guide to the day in national politics. I’m Lisa Lerer, your host.
